                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script" cert="medium">Second half of the 17th century–first half of the 18th century-script (?).</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (crimson on <locus target="#23v #42r"/>)</seg>.
                        <desc>Fine, careful. Same scribe as manuscript <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESdd030">Bǝḥerāwi Kǝllǝlāwi Mangǝśti Tǝgrāy, Dabra Dāmmo ʾAbuna ʾAragāwi, DD-030</ref>.
                           The scribe reduced the size of his handwriting to accommodate the end of the line: <locus target="#5v #38r #39r #57r #98r #103r #110v #119v #121r"/>.
                           Part of the line is taken up on <locus target="#8r #76r #83v"/>.</desc>
                        
